				<td>
				    Five students from grade 5, three students from grade 8, and four students from grade 10 and 2 students from 12th grade passed the Centralized Sunday School Examination of the North East American Diocese. Angelle Philip and Jonathan Kurian shared the third rank and Stephen John scored fourth rank in the centralized examination. Timothy Mathew and Nizy Roy made history by appearing in the 12th grade Centralized Examination for the first time from our church. Timothy won the third rank in the Diocese. Also Aju Tharian passed the Teacher Training Certificate (TTC) examination. To encourage our Sunday school children, we have introduced cash awards from our church sponsors for the highest scoring children in fifth, eighth and tenth grade centralized examinations. These children should score 80 or more to be eligible for this award. This year, Mrs.Ponnama Mammen Memorial $ 50 each cash awards sponsored by Johnson Thomas & family were given to Angelle Philip and Jonathan Kurian from the 5th grade, Mr.O.M.Kunjukunju $100 cash award sponsored by Titus Mathew & family was given to George Varghese from 8th grade and Mr & Mrs.T. K. Mathew Memorial $100 cash award sponsored by Mr. Abey K. Tharian & family was given to Rinsu George from the 10th grade.
				</td>
